{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d090fc83-13ce-44bf-b80c-bd6231961a32","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose fully qualified name contains that string. The `~` operator means \"contains\".\n\nNow every time you save a change, only that single test will re-run.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b14cf50-5090-42f0-af4c-dc53753eeccd","outputTokens":137},"id":"e94f87e6-8b44-493a-a8e5-abfef0ffc2ff","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:58:27.998Z","parentId":"2277f327-273d-4f61-b150-fc1211dfeb8f"}
